Comb B Ising Model Coursework

This notebook uses the data extracted from the Ising Model that was made in C++ and shows the analysis from said data.

The Coursework was split into 5 questions:

Q1a - Calculating average magnetisation and how it changes with an increasing sweep number

Q1b - Calculating average energy and how it changes with an increasing sweep number

Q2 - Analysing how magnetisation and energy change when beta (inverse of temperature) increases

Q3 + 4 - Comparing data from a mean field approximation (MFA) with the data from the Ising Model

Q5 - Determining the relationship between the G_ij coefficient and the distance d between particles

Question 1a¶

Calculating the average magnetisation of the Ising Model and its relationship to an increasing sweep number.

#Formatting function

def format(xlabel, ylabel):
    plt.xlabel(xlabel, fontname="Times New Roman", fontsize=12)
    plt.ylabel(ylabel, fontname="Times New Roman", fontsize=12)
    plt.rcParams["font.family"] = "Times New Roman"
    plt.xticks(fontname="Times New Roman")
    plt.yticks(fontname="Times New Roman")
    return

#Reading in the data for Magnetisation at different temperatures
df_m = pd.read_table("C:\\Users\\euanc\\OneDrive - University of Bath\\Documents\\Work\\Final Year\\2nd semester\\CompB\\Ising Model\\Raw Data\\Mag1500.txt", 
                    delimiter = ",", header = None, names= ["Beta", "Sweep no.", "M"])

b1 = [0.248, 0.328, 0.408, 0.44, 0.6, 0.696] #Beta values we want to look at

#Modified dataset, only shows sweep numbers that are a multiple of 10, starts from 0
df_mod_m = df_m[df_m["Sweep no."] % 10 == 0]
df_mod_m = df_mod_m.loc[df_m['Beta'].isin(b1)]

# Calculating the mean value for the magnetisation for each sweep number in a given beta value, then plotting
mean_m = df_mod_m.groupby(by=["Beta", "Sweep no."],
                          as_index=False).mean("M")

mean_m = mean_m.pivot(index='Sweep no.', columns='Beta', values='M').plot()
format("Sweep No.", r"$\langle$M$\rangle$")
plt.legend(b1, loc="right", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.33), 
            frameon=False, fontsize=12)

# Error in E, M  and |M| against beta
m_err = df_m2.groupby(["Beta"])["M"].sem()
e2_err = df_e2.groupby(["Beta"])["E"].sem()
ab_m_err = df_ab.groupby(["Beta"])["M"].sem()

# List for legend
leg = [r"$\langle$M$\rangle$", r"$\langle$E/(NJ)$\rangle$",
       r"$\langle$$\|$M$\|$$\rangle$"]

# Plotting the three error trends
ax = m_err.plot(x='Beta', y='M')
e2_err.plot(ax=ax, x='Beta', y='E')
ab_m_err.plot(ax=ax, x='Beta', y='|M|')

# Formatting
format("Beta", "Standard Error")
plt.legend(leg, frameon=False, fontsize=12)
plt.show()

#Approx. sinh models
def mPos(B):
    return (1 - (1/((np.sinh(2 * B))**4)))**(1/8)


def mNeg(B):
    return -(1 - (1/((np.sinh(2 * B))**4)))**(1/8)
